What’s actually happening under the hood

1) Attention capture (the entry point)

* Bright screens, motion, novelty → grab your eyes
* Notifications → interrupt your current task
* Infinite scroll → removes natural stopping points

This is just stimulus design, not hypnosis.

⸻

2) Reward loops (why you stay)

* Likes, comments, new content = variable rewards
* Same principle as slot machines (unpredictable payoff)

Your brain learns:

“maybe the next scroll will be good”

That uncertainty is what keeps you hooked.

⸻

3) Personalization (why it feels “targeted”)

* Algorithms learn what you pause on, like, share
* They feed you more of that → tighter loop over time

It’s not reading your mind—it’s tracking behavior patterns extremely well.

⸻

4) Behavior shaping (the downstream effect)

Over time, this leads to:

* shorter attention spans
* habit formation
* subtle shifts in preferences and beliefs

But this is still:

probability nudging, not direct control

⸻

